> The design in the draft is aligned with the practices, e.g., in https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc5575.
> 
> I have a concern with the proposed changes as they cannot allow to enforce policies on the flags that are not currently assigned by IANA. This is problematic.

The current implementations are highly alligned with the identity kind of behavior, and can clarify its usability.

Juniper [ref](https://www.juniper.net/documentation/us/en/software/junos/idp-policy/topics/ref/statement/security-edit-tcp-flags.html):
```
tcp-flags {
    (ack | no-ack);
    (fin | no-fin);
    (psh | no-psh);
    (r1 | no-r1);
    (r2 | no-r2);
    (rst | no-rst);
    (syn | no-syn);
    (urg | no-urg);
} 
```

